title: From NWA to South Central MS
name: From NWA to South Central MS
description:
A Map by Xyzzy32

My typical route to drive to Mississippi to vist the folks.

properties.name: East on I 20
properties.description: Posted by Xyzzy32VicksburgNow it\'s East on I20. Traffic is often heavy just east of Vicksburg.

properties.name: Grady Speed Trap
properties.description: Posted by Xyzzy32Grady ArBe sure the to observe the speed limit through Grady.

properties.name: I540 and I40
properties.description: Posted by Xyzzy32Alma ArInteresection of I540 and I40, although Google earth doesn\'t seem to know about I540 yet.

properties.name: Pine Bluff Bypass
properties.description: Posted by Xyzzy32Pine Bluff ARThe Pine Bluff Bypass was a great addition to the trip. Beats driving through Pine Bluff.

properties.name: South on Highway 1
properties.description: Posted by Xyzzy32Greenvile Ms 2Highway 1 South

properties.name: South on Highway 65
properties.description: Posted by Xyzzy32Little Rock ARIn Little Rock you turn right to get on Highway 65 south.

properties.name: Stay on 65/82
properties.description: Posted by Xyzzy32Lake Villiage ARThe wife likes to continue on south here through Louisiana. Not me. I prefer to cross the bridge into MS here.

properties.name: Take Highway 454 to Highway 1
properties.description: Posted by Xyzzy32Greenvile MsA short little road that takes you to Highway 1

properties.name: Turn left or east on Highway 14
properties.description: Posted by Xyzzy32Highway 1 and Highway 14We\'re only on 14 for a short while before turning right. If you miss the turn, you\'ll end up in Rolling Fork. Just run right on 61 if you do.

properties.name: Turn right on the first road you see
properties.description: Posted by Xyzzy32Little road not on mapJust before you get to Rolling Fork, there\'s a little road to the right. It doesn\'t show up on this map, but trust me it\'s there. Take this road and you will come out on Highway 61 and not have to drive through Rolling Fork.

properties.name: Turn right to go south on Highway 61
properties.description: Posted by Xyzzy32Highway 61 southNow you\'re on Highway 61, the Blues Highway
